  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nIf running the beacon node with the `--slasher` option, when stopping the beacon node, a panic may occur.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\n```text\r\nNot sure.\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### ðŸ”¬ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Start a beacon node with the `--slasher` option.\r\n- Wait a little bit, then press `Ctrl-C`.\r\n\r\n### Error\r\n\r\n```text\r\nfatal error: concurrent map iteration and map write\r\ngoroutine 178331 [running]:\r\ngithub.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/v4/beacon-chain/db/slasherkv.(*Store).SaveLastEpochsWrittenForValidators(0x1400038ede0, {0x1065d0748, 0x14074f12690}, 0x140153ad6e0)\r\n\tbeacon-chain/db/slasherkv/slasher.go:70 +0x158\r\ngithub.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/v4/beacon-chain/slasher.(*Service).Stop(0x14030880100)\r\n\tbeacon-chain/slasher/service.go:159 +0x124\r\ngithub.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/v4/runtime.(*ServiceRegistry).StopAll(0x140004dbc40)\r\n\truntime/service_registry.go:56 +0x90\r\ngithub.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/v4/beacon-chain/node.(*BeaconNode).Close(0x140006029c0)\r\n\tbeacon-chain/node/node.go:384 +0xac\r\n...\r\n```\r\n### Platform(s)\r\n\r\nLinux (ARM)\r\n\r\n### What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)\r\n\r\ndevelop\r\n",
